HEADWORD: Water gruel
<hw>Wa"ter gru"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A liquid food composed of
water and a small portion of meal, or other farinaceous substance,
boiled and seasoned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

